679 // Transform as below.

2466 331754 void moveConcat(AstConcat* nodep) {
2467 // 1: CONCAT(CONCAT({a},{b}),{c}) -> CONCAT({a},CONCAT({b}, {c}))
2468 // or 2: CONCAT({a}, CONCAT({b},{c})) -> CONCAT(CONCAT({a},{b}),{c})
2469 // Because the lhs of a concat needs a shift but the rhs doesn't,
2470 // putting additional CONCATs on the RHS leads to fewer assembler operations.
2471 // However, we'll end up with lots of wide moves if we make huge trees
